  "issue_number": 194,
  "issue_title": "feat: `vouch review-ui` \u2014 browser-based review console [VEP]",
  "issue_body": "**Labels:** enhancement, VEP\n\n**What you're trying to do**\n\nThe review gate is vouch's load-bearing primitive, but the only way to drive it today is the terminal (`vouch list-pending`, `vouch approve <id>`). That works for a solo CLI user; it breaks the moment two reviewers share a KB or the queue grows past ~20 items. Add a browser console that runs over `vouch serve --transport http` (#1) and renders the queue, diff, audit trail, and one-click approve/reject. The CLI stays untouched \u2014 this is an additional viewport on the same `kb.*` surface.\n\n**Suggested shape**\n\n```bash\nvouch review-ui                      # binds 127.0.0.1:7780, opens browser\nvouch review-ui --bind 0.0.0.0:7780  # team mode, errors without --auth bearer\n```\n\n- New `src/vouch/web/`: FastAPI app + Jinja2 templates + HTMX frontend. No React, no build step.\n- Every action goes through the existing `storage.py` / `proposals.py` / `lifecycle.py` handlers \u2014 the web layer is a viewport, not a parallel data path. Same code path as the CLI, same audit-log entry.\n- Single WebSocket channel per KB so two reviewers stay in sync without manual refresh.\n- Reviewer identity comes from the Bearer token (depends on #1 + #2).\n- Views: `/` queue, `/claim/<id>`, `/session/<id>` (proposals grouped by agent run), `/audit`, `/sources/<id>` (reverse index).\n- Static assets ship inside the wheel; no `npm install`, no CDN.\n\n**Acceptance**\n\n- `vouch review-ui` against a fresh KB starts a server, opens the browser, renders the queue.\n- Two browser windows on the same KB stay in sync within 1s via WebSocket.\n- A 500-item queue first-page renders in <200ms (server-side paginated).\n- Disabling JS still lets you read claims and approve via plain form POST.\n- E2E smoke test (`pytest tests/test_web_e2e.py`) drives the approve flow and asserts an `audit.log.jsonl` entry lands.\n- Same `0.0.0.0`-without-`--auth bearer` refusal as #1.\n\n**Out of scope**\n\n- Hosted \"vouch cloud\" SaaS \u2014 this is local/self-hosted only.\n- Free-form claim editing in the browser; the gate is approve / reject / contradict / supersede.\n- Auth beyond Bearer (OAuth/SSO can layer on later).\n- Deleting durable claims from the UI; that stays CLI-only so a misclick can't blow away history.\n\nZero new on-disk schema, zero new `kb.*` methods, zero CLI breakage.\n\n---\n\n**Honorable mentions** (didn't make the 10 but worth filing later):\nGitHub Action `vouchdev/setup-vouch@v1` \u00b7 `ghcr.io/vouchdev/vouch` Docker + devcontainer feature \u00b7 Claude Desktop `.mcpb` extension \u00b7 `vouch ingest --from-pr <url>` \u00b7 gpg-signed bundles \u00b7 `adapters/agent-sdk/` quickstarts \u00b7 MCP Apps UI surface for Cursor.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-10T15:24:19.000Z",
